@Them _" ... a hacker is someone who uses code and tech interface to do illegal stuff .."_

Yes, and no. 

The word has multiple senses (which is a very normal feature of natural language -- it's called "polysemy"). The sense of someone doing something illegal is more recent, and is used more among people who are not programmers -- especially in the media. The older sense is something like _someone who makes systems do things they were not exactly designed to do._  That sense doesn't really have a negative connotation, and is more commonly used by people who actually no what they are talking about -- programmers.
